<p>
<seg id=1> Tang Jiaxuan, Chinese Foreign Minister who is now visiting the US, and Albright, Secretary of State of the US, jointly held a press conference in Washington on 29th and each gave a speech on the issue of the Sino-US relation. </seg>
<seg id=2> Tang Jiaxuan also mentioned that the sex scandal of President Clinton is the internal affair of the USA, and that China would never forget his contribution to the promotion of Sino-US friendship. </seg>
<seg id=3> The following is the report of the interviews made by VOA reporter Zhou Youkang at the press conference that day. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Ladies and gentlemen, US President Clinton met at the White House at 11:30 on the morning of 29th with Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan who is now paying an official visit to Washington. </seg>
<seg id=5> At the joint press conference held by Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and the State Council on the noon of 29th, Secretary of State Albright announced the news of President Clinton's meeting with Tang Jiaxuan. </seg>
<seg id=6> Albright said, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Secretary of State Albright said, I am very glad to tell you that Foreign Minister Tang just met with President Clinton; and she announced that China had decided to sign an international treaty of citizen right and political right in New York on October 5th. </seg>
<seg id=8> Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan also stated at the press conference that his being able to meet with Clinton is really significant. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> President Clinton met with me, and I think our meeting is productive. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> President Clinton is having a very troublesome time at the moment, and many people in and outside the US expressed their strong resentment and criticism to President Clinton because of his sex scandal. </seg>
<seg id=11> Some proposed to impeach him, some wanted him to resign voluntarily, and even some Democratic Congressmen wanted to make a clean break with him. </seg>
<seg id=12> However, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan did not mind this at all; instead, he lauded and praised President Clinton's contribution to the promotion of Sino-US relation. </seg>
<seg id=13> Right at the press conference, a reporter questioned Tang Jiaxuan whether President Clinton's sex scandal would affect the relation between China and USA. </seg>
<seg id=14> Tang Jiaxuan said the following: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=15> I think that this question of affection is entirely USA's internal question. </seg>
<seg id=16> I've never thought that this will have any effect on the development of Sino-US relation. </seg>
<seg id=17> President Clinton himself has made important and precious contributions to the development of Sino-US relation, and we will never forget the contributions he made. </seg>
<seg id=18> Personally, as China's Foreign Minister, I expect cordially that the Sino-US relationship will continue to progress steadily and substantially on the basis of the three Sino-US Joint Communiques and the joint statement made by the heads of the two countries this time. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=19> The authorities of the Chinese Communist Party reiterated time and again that Taiwan is a province of China, and that the issue of Taiwan is China's internal affair. </seg>
<seg id=20> At the United Nations' conference that he attended and on several public occasions during his visit to Washington, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan spoke of the issue of Taiwan  again and again. </seg>
<seg id=21> Right at the press conference, a reporter asked Tang Jiaxuan what the biggest barrier is for the Sino-US strategic partnership at present; Tang answered as follows: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=22> I think we have talked about this many times; what we must pay special attention to at this point is the necessity of properly handling the issue of Taiwan. </seg>
<seg id=23> Because the issue of Taiwan is the most sensitive as well as the most realistic part of the Sino-US relation. </seg>
</p>
